.TH EYEMOUSE 1 "2026" "tobii4c" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
eyemouse \- Tobii Eye Tracker X11 mouse control

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B eyemouse
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ config_file ]

.SH DESCRIPTION

.B eyemouse
reads Tobii gaze coordinates and maps them to the X11 mouse cursor.

The current implementation uses:

.IP \(bu 4
3x3 mesh calibration

.IP \(bu 4
Barycentric triangle interpolation

.IP \(bu 4
Light gaze smoothing

.IP \(bu 4
Exclusive Quha device grab via EVIOCGRAB (always active)

.IP \(bu 4
Optional Quha gyroscopic fine correction

.IP \(bu 4
Automatic Quha device detection through
.I /dev/input/by-id

.IP \(bu 4
X11 pointer warping

.SH OPTIONS

.TP
.B -h, --help
Show command line help.

.TP
.B --usegyro
Enable Quha gyroscopic fine correction input.

.TP
.B --debug
Enable verbose debug output on stderr.
Covers initialisation, Quha grab, gyro events, and XWarpPointer calls.
Output lines are prefixed with
.BR [DBG] .

.TP
.B --debuggaze
Enable verbose gaze output on stderr.
Covers every gaze sample, triangle selection, barycentric coordinates,
warp output, and per-frame cursor state.
Output lines are prefixed with
.BR [GAZE] .
This flag is high frequency (~90 Hz) and should be redirected to a file
when used together with
.BR --debug .

.TP
.B --debuggyro
Enable verbose gyro event output on stderr.
Covers every REL_X and REL_Y event received from the Quha device,
with raw value and accumulated gyro offset.
Output lines are prefixed with
.BR [GYRO] .
This flag is high frequency and should be redirected to a file
when used together with other debug flags.

.TP
.B --blink
Enable blink click gesture recognition.
A short blink triggers a left click, a medium blink triggers a right click,
and a long blink toggles mouse button hold for drag operations.

.TP
.BI --blink-left " ms"
Left click blink duration threshold in milliseconds (default: 80).
Blinks shorter than this value are treated as noise and ignored.

.TP
.BI --blink-right " ms"
Right click blink duration threshold in milliseconds (default: 300).
Blinks between
.B --blink-left
and this value trigger a left click.
Blinks between this value and
.B --blink-hold
trigger a right click.

.TP
.BI --blink-hold " ms"
Hold toggle blink duration threshold in milliseconds (default: 600).
Blinks at or above this duration toggle mouse button hold on/off.

.TP
.B --debugblink
Enable verbose blink event output on stderr.
Covers eye open/close events, blink duration, and action taken.
Output lines are prefixed with
.BR [BLINK] .

.TP
.BI config_file
Optional calibration file path.

If omitted, the default calibration file is used:

.EX
~/.local/tobii_4c/calx11.conf
.EE

.SH CALIBRATION FORMAT

The calibration file contains exactly 9 calibration points.

Each line contains:

.EX
raw_x raw_y target_x target_y
.EE

Example:

.EX
0.028959 0.022570 0.030000 0.030000
0.494846 0.025340 0.500000 0.030000
0.980519 -0.010076 0.970000 0.030000
.EE

.SH MESH WARP

The screen is divided into a 3x3 calibration mesh.

Each quad is internally split into triangles.

The runtime mapping uses barycentric interpolation inside
the triangle mesh to transform raw Tobii gaze coordinates
into calibrated screen coordinates.

This improves edge accuracy compared to simple affine
transforms.

.SH QUHA SUPPORT

The Quha device is automatically detected through:

.EX
/dev/input/by-id
.EE

The Quha device is grabbed exclusively using EVIOCGRAB whenever
eyemouse starts, regardless of whether
.B --usegyro
is active.
This prevents X11 from receiving raw Quha mouse events in parallel
while eyemouse controls the cursor.

If the exclusive grab fails, a warning is printed and eyemouse
continues running, but X11 may still receive Quha events simultaneously.

On SIGTERM, SIGINT, or SIGHUP the grab is released automatically
before exit, so the Quha resumes normal X11 mouse operation immediately.

.SS Gyro mode

When
.B --usegyro
is active, Quha movement events are additionally read and applied
as a relative fine correction on top of the Tobii gaze position.
The offset decays exponentially (factor 0.92 per frame), so gaze
remains the primary positioning input.

.SH BLINK CLICK

When
.B --blink
is active, eye blink duration determines the mouse action:

.TS
l l.
Duration	Action
_
< --blink-left (80ms)	Noise, ignored
80ms \(en 300ms	Left click
300ms \(en 600ms	Right click
\(>= 600ms	Hold toggle
.TE

Hold toggle alternately presses and releases the left mouse button,
enabling drag operations without physical input.

Requires
.I libXtst
at build time
.RB ( \-lXtst ).

.SH FILES

.TP
.I ~/.local/tobii_4c/calx11.conf
Default calibration file.

.SH EXAMPLES

Default calibration:

.EX
eyemouse
.EE

Custom calibration:

.EX
eyemouse tobii.conf
.EE

Enable Quha gyro:

.EX
eyemouse --usegyro
.EE

Custom calibration with gyro:

.EX
eyemouse --usegyro tobii.conf
.EE

Debug mode:

.EX
eyemouse --debug
.EE

Gaze debug (high frequency):

.EX
eyemouse --debuggaze
.EE

Enable blink click:

.EX
eyemouse --blink
.EE

Blink with custom thresholds:

.EX
eyemouse --blink --blink-left 100 --blink-right 350 --blink-hold 650
.EE

Blink and gyro combined:

.EX
eyemouse --blink --usegyro
.EE

Blink debug:

.EX
eyemouse --blink --debugblink
.EE

All debug output to log file:

.EX
eyemouse --debug --debuggaze --debuggyro --debugblink 2>eyemouse.log
.EE

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR eyecalib (1)

